      • isTouchingActor

        public boolean[] isTouchingActor(Actor a)
        Determines if the actor passed is touching the wall, and if so, then in what direction.
        Parameters:
        a - the actor to which this wall might touch.
        Returns:
        a boolean array of size 5, that represents whether an actor is touching a wall Position 0 of the array represents whether the wall is touching the actor Position 1 of the array represents whether the actor is touching the wall from above. Position 2 of the array represents whether the actor is touching the wall from the right. Position 3 of the array represents whether the actor is touching the wall from the bottom Position 4 of the array represents whether the actor is touching the wall from the left.
